## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Azure AD App Registration** — You will need to register an app in Azure Portal (Entra ID) with the following:
> - **Platform**: Mobile and desktop applications
> - **Redirect URI**: `msauth://com.yourorg.livetracking/callback` (for MSAL) or `https://auth.expo.io/@your-expo-username/live-tracking` (for expo-auth-session)
> - **API Permissions**: `Dynamics CRM → user_impersonation`
> - **Tenant ID**, **Client ID** will be needed in the app config

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **D365 Custom Entity** — We need to create a custom entity in CRM to store location data. I propose the entity name `rmt_livetracking` with a display name "Live Tracking". Please confirm:
> 1. Your CRM publisher prefix (I'll use `rmt_` as placeholder)
> 2. Whether you want the tracking data entity to be activity-enabled or a plain custom entity

> [!WARNING]
> **Background Location on iOS** — Apple requires a justification string (`NSLocationAlwaysAndWhenInUseUsageDescription`) for App Store submission. Background location tracking must clearly benefit the user, and Apple reviews this carefully.

