#### [NEW] `src/auth/AuthProvider.tsx` — Authentication Context

- Wraps the app with MSAL provider
- Exposes `login()`, `logout()`, `getToken()`, `user` state
- Handles token refresh automatically
- Stores tokens securely with `expo-secure-store`

---

#### [NEW] `src/services/LocationService.ts` — Location Tracking Engine

Core tracking service with these features:

| Feature | Implementation |
|---|---|
| **High accuracy** | `accuracy: Location.Accuracy.BestForNavigation` |
| **No caching** | `mayShowUserSettingsDialog: true`, fresh GPS fix each time |
| **Frequent updates** | `timeInterval: 5000` (5s), `distanceInterval: 2` (2m) |
| **Small movements** | Low `distanceInterval` threshold |
| **Background tracking** | `expo-task-manager` with `startLocationUpdatesAsync` |
| **Batching** | Queue locations locally, flush to CRM every 10-15s |
| **Distance calc** | Haversine formula between consecutive points |

```typescript
// Foreground tracking config
const LOCATION_OPTIONS = {
  accuracy: Location.Accuracy.BestForNavigation,
  timeInterval: 5000,
  distanceInterval: 2,
  mayShowUserSettingsDialog: true,
};

// Background tracking task
TaskManager.defineTask(LOCATION_TASK_NAME, ({ data, error }) => {
  if (data) {
    const { locations } = data;
    LocationQueue.enqueue(locations);
  }
});
```

---

#### [NEW] `src/services/D365Client.ts` — Dynamics 365 Web API Client

- Authenticated REST client using bearer tokens from MSAL
- CRUD operations for the custom tracking entity
- Batch API support for posting multiple location records at once
- Retry logic with exponential backoff
- Offline queue (locations stored locally when no network)

```typescript
class D365Client {
  async createTrackingRecord(data: TrackingRecord): Promise<void> { }
  async batchCreateRecords(records: TrackingRecord[]): Promise<void> { }
  async getTrackingHistory(userId: string, date: Date): Promise<TrackingRecord[]> { }
}
```

