### Component 2: D365 CRM Custom Entity

#### `rmt_livetracking` Entity Schema

| Field | Type | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `rmt_livetrackingid` | Uniqueidentifier (PK) | Auto-generated |
| `rmt_name` | Single Line Text | Auto-generated identifier |
| `rmt_latitude` | Decimal (precision: 10) | GPS latitude |
| `rmt_longitude` | Decimal (precision: 10) | GPS longitude |
| `rmt_altitude` | Decimal | Altitude in meters |
| `rmt_speed` | Decimal | Speed in m/s |
| `rmt_heading` | Decimal | Compass heading (0-360) |
| `rmt_accuracy` | Decimal | GPS accuracy in meters |
| `rmt_timestamp` | DateTime | UTC timestamp of the fix |
| `rmt_sessionid` | Single Line Text | Groups locations in a session |
| `rmt_distance` | Decimal | Cumulative distance in km |
| `rmt_devicetype` | OptionSet | Android / iOS |
| `rmt_batteryLevel` | Whole Number | Device battery % |
| `rmt_userid` | Lookup (systemuser) | CRM user reference |

> [!NOTE]
> This entity will be documented with step-by-step creation instructions. We can also provide a CRM solution XML for easy import.

---

### Component 3: Azure Maps Web Resource

#### [NEW] `crm-webresource/html/LiveTrackingMap.html`

A standalone HTML page embedded as a D365 web resource, using:
- **Azure Maps Web SDK** for rendering
- **D365 Web API (Xrm.WebApi)** for fetching tracking data from CRM
- **Auto-refresh** (polling every 10-15s) for near-real-time updates

**Key features:**

| Feature | Description |
|---|---|
| **Live markers** | Each tracked user shown as a marker with name label |
| **Location trail** | Polyline showing movement history |
| **User panel** | Sidebar listing all active users with status |
| **Metrics overlay** | Distance covered, time elapsed, average speed |
| **Auto-center** | Map auto-fits to show all active users |
| **Date filter** | View historical tracking data by date |
| **Clustering** | Cluster markers when zoomed out |
| **User colors** | Each user gets a distinct color for their trail |

```html
<!-- Azure Maps SDK -->
<link rel="stylesheet" href="https://atlas.microsoft.com/sdk/javascript/mapcontrol/3/atlas.min.css" />
<script src="https://atlas.microsoft.com/sdk/javascript/mapcontrol/3/atlas.min.js"></script>
```

