## Architecture Highlights

### Data Flow
```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant App as 📱 Mobile App
    participant AD as 🔐 Azure AD
    participant CRM as 📦 D365 CRM
    participant Map as 🗺️ Azure Maps

    App->>AD: Login (MSAL)
    AD-->>App: Access Token
    
    loop Every 5-10 seconds
        App->>App: Get GPS Location
        App->>CRM: POST /api/data/v9.2/rmt_livetrackings
        Note over App,CRM: Bearer token + Location JSON
    end
    
    Map->>CRM: GET /api/data/v9.2/rmt_livetrackings?$filter=...
    Note over CRM,Map: Fetch active tracking records
    Map->>Map: Render markers & trails
```

### Scalability Considerations
- **Batching**: Mobile app batches 3-5 locations per API call instead of 1:1
- **D365 Batch API**: Uses `$batch` endpoint to reduce HTTP calls
- **Polling vs WebSockets**: Start with polling (simpler in CRM context); can add Azure SignalR later if needed
- **Data retention**: Consider archiving old tracking records (Power Automate flow to archive after N days)

### Battery Optimization
- Adaptive tracking interval based on movement speed
- Reduce accuracy when stationary (switch from BestForNavigation to Balanced)
- Background tracking uses `deferredUpdatesInterval` on iOS

---

## Additional Suggestions

1. **Geofencing** — Add geofence alerts when users enter/exit predefined areas
2. **Check-in/Check-out** — Auto-log when users arrive at or leave customer locations
3. **Offline Mode** — Queue locations in SQLite when offline, sync when back online
4. **Push Notifications** — Notify admins when a user goes offline or leaves a geofence
5. **Analytics Dashboard** — Power BI dashboard for historical tracking analytics
6. **Privacy Controls** — Allow users to pause tracking (with admin visibility)

